      <p>We thrive in information-thick worlds because of our marvelous and everyday 
      capacity to select, edit, single out, structure, highlight, group, pair, merge, 
      harmonize, synthesize, focus, organize, condense, reduce, boil down, choose, 
      categorize, catalog, classify, list, abstract, scan, look into, idealize,<footnote>Ideal&mdash;see 
      <a href="http://classics.mit.edu/Plato/">Plato</a></footnote> isolate, 
      discriminate, distinguish, screen, pigeonhole, pick over, sort, integrate, blend, 
      inspect, filter, lump, skip, smooth, chunk, average, approximate, cluster, aggregate, 
      outline, summarize, itemize, review, dip into, flip through, browse, glance 
      into, leaf through, skim, refine, enumerate, glean, synopsize, winnow the wheat 
      from the chaff and separate the sheep from the goats. </p>
